article.description: Brandon Anderson had 20 points as Brown topped Columbia 72-66 on Friday night.
article.headline: Anderson scores 20 as Brown tops Columbia 72-66
article.linkText: Anderson scores 20 as Brown tops Columbia 72-66
article.story: NEW YORK -- Brandon Anderson had 20 points as Brown topped Columbia 72-66 on Friday night. Zach Hunsaker had 17 points for Brown (13-9, 6-3 Ivy League). Tamenang Choh added 15 points, seven rebounds and six assists. Jaylan Gainey had 10 points and 12 rebounds. The Bears are in a three-way for second place with Princeton and Harvard, a game behind Yale (7-2). Mike Smith had 22 points for the Lions (6-19, 1-8), who have lost eight straight games. Jake Killingsworth added 16 points and six rebounds. Tai Bibbs had 11 points and seven rebounds. The Bears improve to 2-0 against the Lions this season. Brown defeated Columbia 72-66 on Feb. 1. Brown takes on Cornell on the road on Saturday. Columbia plays Yale at home on Saturday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
